---
import PublicPageLayout from './PublicPageLayout.astro';

const { canonicalPath = '/terms' } = Astro.props;
const LAST_UPDATED = '17 July 2026';
const LAST_UPDATED_ISO = '2026-07-17';
---

<PublicPageLayout
    pageKey="terms"
    title="Terms & Conditions"
    summary="These are the ground rules for using TaskTime Pro. The short version: your data is yours, the app is provided as-is, and you are responsible for your own records and backups."
    lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
    lastUpdatedIso={LAST_UPDATED_ISO}
    highlights={[
        'TaskTime Pro is local-first — work records live in your browser and, optionally, your own Google Drive.',
        'The app is provided as-is without warranties. Keep your own backups.',
        'Liability is limited to the fullest extent permitted by law.',
    ]}
    canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
>
    <section>
        <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
        <p>
            By using TaskTime Pro you agree to these terms. If you don&apos;t agree, don&apos;t use the app.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>2. What TaskTime Pro is</h2>
        <p>
            TaskTime Pro is a local-first productivity app for freelancers. It helps you track time, manage tasks and expenses, and generate invoices. Core use runs in your browser and stores work records on your device. There is no required TaskTime account or TaskTime-hosted workspace database.
        </p>
        <p>
            TaskTime Pro is a tool, not professional advice. You are responsible for reviewing anything you create, export, or send &mdash; including invoices, time records, and expense reports.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>3. Your data, your responsibility</h2>
        <p>
            Because your work records live primarily in your browser (and optionally in your own Google Drive), you are responsible for keeping backups, maintaining accurate records, and securing your devices and accounts. If you clear your browser data and have no sync or export, that data is gone &mdash; we cannot recover it because TaskTime Pro does not maintain a hosted workspace copy.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>4. Google Drive sync</h2>
        <p>
            Google Drive sync is optional. When enabled, it stores sync documents in <strong>your own</strong> Google Drive account. Routine sync file requests travel directly between your browser and Google Drive. TaskTime Pro&apos;s edge service securely maintains the Google connection and issues a short-lived browser token, but does not receive routine Drive file bodies. The sync feature depends on Google&apos;s and Cloudflare&apos;s services and is governed by their applicable terms and privacy policies. We are not responsible for their availability, outages, or policy changes.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>5. Invoice email sending</h2>
        <p>
            The Send Invoice feature delivers emails via <strong>Resend</strong> (resend.com), a third-party email delivery service. By using this feature you agree to Resend&apos;s <a href="https://resend.com/legal/terms-of-service" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">terms of service</a> and <a href="https://resend.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Email delivery is subject to a monthly limit per account. We do not guarantee delivery &mdash; factors outside our control, such as recipient spam filters or service availability, may prevent emails from arriving. You are responsible for confirming receipt with your clients. Do not use this feature to send unsolicited messages.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>6. No warranties</h2>
        <p>
            TaskTime Pro is provided as-is and as-available. To the fullest extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties &mdash; express, implied, or statutory &mdash; including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy, reliability, and uninterrupted operation.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>7. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, TaskTime Pro and its operator will not be liable for data loss, sync failures, corrupted records, interrupted business, lost profits, or any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the app.
        </p>
        <p>
            Where liability cannot be fully excluded by law, total liability is limited to the amount you paid for TaskTime Pro in the twelve months before the event &mdash; which may be zero.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>8. Changes and availability</h2>
        <p>
            TaskTime Pro may be updated, changed, or discontinued at any time. Features &mdash; including sync behavior and supported integrations &mdash; may evolve. Keep your own backups of anything important.
        </p>
        <p>
            We may also introduce paid plans, subscription options, or other payment tiers in the future at our discretion. If we do, the applicable pricing and terms will be presented to you at that time.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>9. Termination</h2>
        <p>
            You can stop using TaskTime Pro at any time. Access to connected features may be restricted or suspended if necessary for security, abuse prevention, or legal reasons.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>10. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
            These terms may be updated as TaskTime Pro evolves. The current version will always be posted here with the date it was last changed. Continued use after an update means you accept the new terms.
        </p>
    </section>
</PublicPageLayout>
